mulation in leaves of leafy vegetables</article-title><source>Ecotoxicol Environ Saf.</source><year>2016</year><volume>123</volume><fpage>89</fpage><lpage>94</lpage><pub-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1016/j.ecoenv.2015.05.019</pub-id><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">26004982</pub-id></element-citation></ref><ref id="CR11"><label>11.</label><mixed-citation publication-type="other">Kumar V, Sah SK, Khare T, Shriram V, Wani SH. Engineering phytohormones for abiotic stress tolerance in crop plants. In: Ahammed GJ, Yu JQ editors.&#x000a0;Plant hormones under challenging environmental factors. Springer Netherlands; 2016. p. 247&#x02013;66.</mixed-citation></ref><ref id="CR12"><label>12.</label><mixed-citation publication-type="other">Mombo S, Foucault Y, Deola F, Gaillard I, Goix S, Shahid M, Schreck E, Pierart A, Dumat C. Management of human health risk in the context of kitchen gardens polluted by lead and cadmium near a lead recycling company. J Soils Sediment. 2015;16:1214&#x02013;24.</mixed-citation></ref><ref id="CR13"><label>13.</label><element-citation publication-type="journal"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Jin</surname><given-names>C</given-names></name><name><surname>Nan</surname><given-names>Z</given-names></name><name><surname>Wang</surname><given-names>H</given-names></name><name><surname>Li</surname><given-names>X</given-names></name><name><surname>Zhou</surname><given-names>J</given-names></name><name><surname>Yao</surname><given-names>X</given-names></name></person-group><article-title>Jin P :Effect of Cd stress on the bioavailability of Cd and other mineral nutrition elements in broad bean grown in a loess subsoil amended with municipal sludge compost</article-title><source>Environ Sci Poll Res.</source><year>2018</year><volume>25</volume><issue>8</issue><fpage>7418</fpage><lpage>7432</lpage><pub-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1007/s11356-017-0994-y</pub-id></element-citation></ref><ref id="CR14"><label>14.</label><element-citation publication-typ